From: HyprWM Fedora maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: find Qt private packages explicitly

Fedora exports Qt6::GuiPrivate and Qt6::WidgetsPrivate from separate CMake
packages. Locate those packages before the platform-theme target links them.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -12,5 +12,7 @@ include(GNUInstallDirs)
 
 find_package(Qt6 6.9 CONFIG REQUIRED COMPONENTS BuildInternals Core Widgets QuickControls2)
+find_package(Qt6GuiPrivate 6.9 CONFIG REQUIRED)
+find_package(Qt6WidgetsPrivate 6.9 CONFIG REQUIRED)
 find_package(PkgConfig REQUIRED)
 find_package(KF6Config REQUIRED)
 find_package(KF6ColorScheme REQUIRED)
